<p sourcefile="articles/finance/asset-leasing/record-rou-asset-depreciation.md" sourcestartlinenumber="66">As was previously mentioned, the straight-line lease expense is calculated as the sum of all payments divided by the lease term. The system automatically calculates the monthly interest expense on the liability amortization schedule. The interest expense is calculated by using the effective interest rate method. The system will use the straight-line lease cost to subtract the interest expense for each month. The value is used to reduce the ROU asset.</p>
